$ Windows thread

{ Thread Information Block (TIB)

  The TIB apparently corresponds to the `NT_TIB` struct (`winnt.h`).

  The TIB is also known as *Thread Environment Block*.
  

}
{ locale

  Each thread is assigned a *locale* which initially is the *system default locale* (`LOCALE_SYSTEM_DEFAULT`, whose value ix 0x0800 ).

  A thread's locale can be changed with the â†’ Windows/development/WinAPI[WinAPI] function `SetThreadLocale`.

}

